{meta: title Broken Engagement}
{meta: artist Webb Pierce}
{meta: writer Wayne P. Walker, Max Powell, Mary Rhodes}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]They were standing in the [G7]moonlight
[C]When he kissed his love goodbye
[G7]He had broken their engagement
[C]And she asked the reason why
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]I have someone else my darling
[C]And she means the world to me
[G7]That is why I'm asking of you
[C]Forgive me dear and set me free
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]Then she whispered oh so [C]sadly
[G7]As the tears they filled her eyes
[C]And his heart was full of [G7]pity
[C]For he took her by surprise
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[G7]If it's true you love another
[C]Better dear than you love me
[G7]Dear I want you to be happy
[C]I’ll forever set you free
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[F]Though you leave me for [C]another
[G7]I hope we'll meet again someday
[C]In that far up home up [G7]yonder
[C]There our love won’t end this way
{end_of_verse}
